diff --git c/.github/workflows/build.yaml i/.github/workflows/build.yaml
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..d250cca
--- /dev/null
+++ i/.github/workflows/build.yaml
@@ -0,0 +1,120 @@
+name: build_document_integrations_lambdas
+run-name: ${{ github.actor }} is building from  ${{ github.ref_name }} branch
+on:
+  push:
+    branches:
+      - main
+      - develop
+      - feature/CAT-132-deployment-pipeline
+
+permissions:
+  id-token: write
+  contents: write
+
+jobs:
+  tag:
+    runs-on: arc-aws-k8s
+    outputs:
+      new_tag: ${{ steps.tag_version.outputs.new_tag }}
+    steps:
+      - name: Auto Bump Version and Tag
+        id: tag_version
+        uses: omflibraries/github-tag-action@v6.1
+        with:
+          github_token: ${{ github.token }}
+          default_bump: patch
+          default_prerelease_bump: prerelease
+          tag_prefix: v
+          release_branches: main
+          create_annotated_tag: false
+          fetch_all_tags: true
+          dry_run: false
+
+  build:
+    needs: tag
+    runs-on:  arc-aws-k8s
+    env:
+      JF_USER: ${{ vars.JF_USER }}
+      AWS_DEFAULT_REGION: ${{ vars.AWS_DEFAULT_REGION }}
+    steps:
+      - name: Install dependencies
+        run: |
+          # Update package list and install curl and unzip
+          sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y curl unzip zip
+      
+          # Install AWS CLI if not present
+          if ! command -v aws &> /dev/null; then
+            echo "AWS CLI not found. Installing..."
+            curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
+            unzip awscliv2.zip
+            sudo ./aws/install
+          else
+            echo "AWS CLI already installed."
+          fi
+
+      - name: Checkout code
+        uses: actions/checkout@v2
+
+      - name: Setup Node.js
+        uses: actions/setup-node@v3
+        with:
+          node-version: '22'
+
+      - name: Install dependencies for document-file-upload
+        run: |
+          cd lambdas/document-file-upload-lambda
+          npm install
+          npm run ci:lint
+          npm run ci:test:unit
+          npm run ci:build
+          cd -
+
+      - name: Package Lambdas
+        run: |
+          for lambda in document-file-upload-lambda; do
+            cd lambdas/$lambda
+            rm -rf node_modules coverage package-lock.json README.md src tests \
+              tsconfig.json tsconfig.prod.json jest.config.ts .eslintrc.json .eslintignore
+            npm install --production
+            mv dist/* .
+            rm -rf dist package-lock.json
+            zip -r ../../${lambda}.zip .
+            cd -
+          done
+
+      - name: Configure AWS credentials
+        id: configure_aws_credentials
+        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v3
+        with:
+          role-to-assume: ${{ vars.AWS_PROD_IAM_ROLE_ARN }}
+          role-session-name: github-action-${{ github.job }}-${{ github.run_id }}
+          aws-region: ${{ env.AWS_DEFAULT_REGION }}
+
+      - name: Get JFrog Secret from AWS Secrets Manager
+        uses: aws-actions/aws-secretsmanager-get-secrets@v1
+        with:
+          secret-ids: |
+            JF_PASSWORD, ${{ vars.JF_SECRET_PATH }}
+          parse-json-secrets: false
+
+      # Install semver CLI version
+      - name: Install semver CLI
+        run: npm install -g semver
+
+      - name: Configure JFrog CLI
+        uses: jfrog/setup-jfrog-cli@v3
+
+      # Upload Authoriser Lambda package to JFrog
+      - name: Upload document-file-upload-lambda to JFrog
+        run: |
+          ls -lha
+          if [ -n "${{ env.JF_PASSWORD }}" ]; then
+            jfrog rt u document-file-upload-lambda.zip "lambdas/document-file-upload-lambda-${{ needs.tag.outputs.new_tag }}.zip"   --url="${{ vars.JF_ARTIFACTORY_URL }}${{ vars.JF_NPM_REPO }}/" --user="${{ env.JF_USER }}" --password="${{ env.JF_PASSWORD }}"
+          else
+            echo "JF_PASSWORD is empty. Please check your secret configuration."
+          fi
+
+      # Summary
+      - name: Add generated version to Job Summary
+        run: |
+          echo "### Generated Version: \`${{ needs.tag.outputs.new_tag }}\`" >> $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY
